verses.roman:
ākāśa--ananta, tāte yaiche pakṣi-gaṇa
yāra yata śakti, tata kare ārohaṇa

synonyms: ākāśa—the sky; ananta—unlimited; tāte—in that sky; yaiche—just as; pakṣi-gaṇa—all types of birds; yāra—of someone; yata śakti—whatever power; tata—that much; kare ārohaṇa—rises up and up.
translation: The sky is unlimited, but many birds fly higher and higher according to their own abilities.
